==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Androgynal
<hw>An*drog"y*nal</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>androgynus</ets>,
Gr. <?/; <grk>'anh`r</grk>, <grk>'andro`s</grk>, man + <grk>gynh`</grk>
woman: cf. F. <ets>androgyne</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Uniting both
sexes in one, or having the characteristics of both; being in nature
both male and female; hermaphroditic.</def> <rj><au>Owen.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The truth is, a great mind must be <qex>androgynous</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Bearing both staminiferous and
pistilliferous flowers in the same cluster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Androgynism</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Androgyny</ent>⟦br⟧
